I want to be able to exclude the audience network traffic in the ad group settings.

To exclude audience network traffic in your ad group settings, you can manage this through the Audience section at the ad set level when creating a campaign. Once your audience data is processed and available, you can select it to include or exclude as needed. For more detailed guidance, you can refer to our article on Audience Management here: [Introduction to Audience Management](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us/articles/26679465558669-Introduction-to-Audience-Management). Let me know if you have any other questions!

NewsBreak Ads Manager offers you the flexibility to reach audiences across various platforms, including NewsBreak itself and other apps within the Audience Network. Please go to our Help Center to submit a ticket to exclude Audience Network traffic if needed

If you need to exclude Audience Network traffic, you can submit a request through our Help Center. You can find the option to submit a ticket there for further assistance. Here's the link to our Help Center: [NewsBreak Help Center](https://help.newsbreak.com/hc/en-us). Let me know if there's anything else I can assist you with!

I'm sorry to hear that the link isn't working for you. You can try accessing the Help Center directly by visiting help.newsbreak.com and navigating to the section where you can submit a request. If you're still having trouble, please let me know, and I'll do my best to assist you further!
If you need to reach out via email for support, you can contact our Ad Support team at adsupport@newsbreak.com. They're available to help with any issues or questions you might have!
